<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARKANSAS BEATS SOUTH ALABAMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PINE BLUFF, Ark. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Larry Marks scored 21 points, including 9 straight during a 16-point Arkansas 
run, and pulled down 12 rebounds to lead the Razorbacks to a 103-71 victory 
over South Alabama Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
Arkansas (6-2) struggled in the first 20 minutes, trailing by as many as 7 
points before rallying to lead the Jaguars (5-4) at halftime, 34-33. 
</P>
<P>
A 24-14 surge early in the second half gave the Razorbacks an 11-point lead. 
Then 16 unanswered points over the next 2 minutes put Arkansas up 76-49. 
</P>
</TEXT>
