CHILE SCHOOL FIRE KILLS 11 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By UPI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTIAGO, Chile 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eleven teen-age boys died and five were injured in a reform school fire that 
was apparently set to cover a mass escape attempt, police said Sunday. 
Eighty-five youths fled in the confusion during the New Year's Eve fire, but 66 
were found immediately. Authorities were searching for the others. 
</P>
