<DATELINE>
<P>
LIMA, Peru 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The New Year roared into Lima on Sunday with a 5.5 magnitude earthquake, right 
on the heels of a blackout believed caused by leftist guerrillas, officials 
said. There were no reports of damage or injury from the temblor. 
</P>
